    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-10T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="326"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20(D)Regulations/2447a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-10T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 10, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. As of assistance in consideration of export license applications for
                    commodities and materials desired by Iranian Government agencies ostensibly for
                    reconstruction activities and for communications and transport the Department
                    desires your opinion whether there is danger of re-exportation of such supplies
                    to Germany via Russia or to Russia. Please telegraph reply promptly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
